HEADWORD: Elaterite
<hw>El"a*ter*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral resin, of a blackish brown color, occurring in soft,
flexible masses; -- called also <altname>mineral caoutchouc</altname>,
and <altname>elastic bitumen</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elaterium</ent>⟦br⟧
